name: Priscilla Riley
review: I use this product everyday from going to work or going to church it adds a natural gleam

name: Jessss
review: THIS IS MY NEW FAVORITE HIGHLIGHTER! I LOVE THE EASY APPLICATION WITH THE STICK AND IT LOOKS AMAZING! PERFECT COVERAGE FOR UNDER EYE HIGHLIGHT AND WHAT NOT!

name: Allie
review: A little too pink but still an easy to apply highlighter for fair skin!

name: Ali
review: I have been searching and searching for just the right highlighting product. I had tried powders, creams, sticks...this one takes the cake! It is the perfect size for getting the color exactly right on my cheekbones, but I can still get the smaller areas like my brow bone and nose. The other thing I LOVE about this product is the bronze color. I debated between the more "pinkish" hue, but went with the bronze color and so happy I did. It looks PERFECT on my tanned skin for summer!

name: Betty's mom
review: I use it around my eyes, down the bridge of my nose, and above my brows.

name: Ns
review: As a highlighter

name: Natural look trendy style
review:
I am in love with this stick! It's so much easier to apply my highlight precisely and have it last all day.
I've always wanted that pretty "cupid's bow" highlight and it never stays because of my Chapstick & lipgloss applications throughout the day but with this highlighter I finally have that stunning look.
Tons of compliments

name: Sol
review: so underrated. so glad i found it. couldn't find any reviews on youtube on this product. took a chance and bought it and it is exactly the highlighter I've been looking for, for the right price. I have light sometimes dry skin and it doesn't look chalky at all which has been an issue for others. def. worth a try

name: bella
review: I usually use it to height light my cheek bones after applying coverup

name: Lex
review: I love this highlighter! My friends wouldn't stop talking about highlighters so I found this one and it's perfect! It is so easy to put on and blends nicely!

name: Ceci J
review: I use this along my cheekbones and down the bridge of my nose. I was disappointed upon first few applications as the texture seemed clumpy and dragged poorly along my skin, smudging foundation and looking unnatural. I later realized that the texture improved drastically when I tapped the product before patting it into my skin and blending with two fingers and repeating for a few minutes. Despite how nice it looked, it's a lot of work for a highlighter that doesn't last long and leaves only obnoxious glitter after glow fades.

name: Amber
review: The product color is nice and glides on smooth, it didn't stay on very long. When I purchased the product it would fall out of container. I feel all the reckon products I have purchased here do this.

name: jojo
review: Drags on skin and moves foundation underneath, not creamy or pigmented enough. Texture is thick and obvious on skin. Pink shade has a strange grey tinge to it (I'm quite pale skinned).

name: Nary-Panama
review: Overall is a good and cheap product... I keep changing brands so it's an economic option!!

name: MakeupFreak101
review: I just use it to highlight ,it's my favorite product

name: Rachelle
review: It's nice for light coverage but doesn't do very well with dry skin. It's decent for an over the counter product

name: Sam
review: I think it didn't work for my complexion  but maybe good for lighter skin

name: Shay
review: Really wanted to try a stick or cream highlighter and it was a toss up between the Maybelliene strobe stick or this. This product swatched well on my hand so I was happy, but that did not translate to my face. It applies well on bare skin but horribly onto foundation. It's streaky and has a lot of drag, i had to try to heat it with the hair dryer to make it glide on smoother. It pulled and dragged off my foundation and looked horrible and would not blend out so it looked like a shiney line on my face. The next day I tried applying before foundation but it just made my foundation sparkly all over and wasn't noticeable in the points I wanted it to be. I like the icy pink color so I gave it 2 stars, good tone for fair, cool skin. the only application I will use this for is my Cupid's bow and in the corners of eyes. Also it is very subtle, so if you like that poppin highlight this isn't for you. Another one bites the dust, to the unused makeup pile this goes! Will try the maybelliene strobe stick as I read it glides on smooth.

name: Blupaizly
review: It's too shimmery for me. I don't want shimmer or sparkle, just plain highlighter.

name: Amy
review: I used this product on top of my bare minerals so that could be the problem but it seemed to rub off my foundation and was difficult to blend. To me it made my makeup look worse and when I went to highlight my nose it totally took my makeup off there too. My boyfriend even commented on how it didn't look good :( would not buy this product again

name: Yer
review: This hilighter works so well if you are looking for a cheap route in a quick finish! Love that you don't need a brush however you may need to use your fingers to blend!

name: Jessica
review: I put this on under my eyes (I don't have dark undereye circles) and use it as a primer. It is so pretty! It adds a beautiful glow to my look without looking unnatural. I really do love it, it looks amazing!

name: HP
review: Highlight

name: La Gioconda
review: Just enough natural, sheer sheen to give a glow to the face. It's easy to apply and blends in well.

name: Beth
review: So pretty! The glow is beautiful!  I pair it with a few other highlights and the glow is real!
